Approach 4: Binary Search on Entire Matrix (Most Optimal)
Intuition

Since the matrix is globally sorted,

1 3 5 7 10 11 16 20 23 30 34 60

we can treat it as a virtual 1D sorted array without creating a new array.

Mapping Formula

Suppose

cols = 4

Then

row = mid / cols

col = mid % cols

Example

mid = 6

row = 6 / 4 = 1

col = 6 % 4 = 2

Matrix

matrix[1][2] = 16
Java (Your Code)
class Solution {

    public boolean searchMatrix(int[][] matrix, int target) {

        int rows = matrix.length;
        int cols = matrix[0].length;

        int left = 0;
        int right = (rows * cols) - 1;

        while (left <= right) {

            int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;

            // Map 1D index to 2D coordinates
            int midValue = matrix[mid / cols][mid % cols];

            if (midValue == target)
                return true;

            else if (midValue < target)
                left = mid + 1;

            else
                right = mid - 1;
        }

        return false;
    }
}
